The **Users **panel allows to view, add and manage local users to the Doxee Platform.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

This view also lists SSO users, identified by the @&lt;domain&gt; indication appended to the username. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

In the current version of the Doxee Platform, local users cannot edit their profile or change their password.

For more information on how to edit user information from the **Settings **service's UI, see [Editing a user](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-users#editing-a-user) and [Generating a new password for a user](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-users#generating-a-new-password-for-a-user) below.

> Note

A user may have multiple roles. By default, users are not associated with any roles. Users that are not associated with any roles cannot access any data on the Doxee Platform.

For more information on how to define and assign roles, see: [Doxee Platform Settings - Roles](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-roles).

### Creating a user
- Click **Add**. The **Create User **form is displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Section**

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**General Information**

**Userna me**

X

Unique username of the new user (a combination of alphanumeric characters, spaces, and special characters)

**Email**

X

Email address of the new user

**First name**

X

The user's first name

**Last name**

X

The user's last name

**Localiza tion**

X

Select the preferred language to view the UI:

**English **

- **Italiano**

**Status**

X

Select the status of the user upon creation:

- **Enabled **

- **Disabled**

**Tags**

**Tags**

Enter one or more tags (up to 10 tags, separated by a comma) to label the user. Tags may have a maximum length of 20 characters.

- Click **Save **to confirm. The system generates a new, temporary password for the user.

> Note

A CSV file named *_&lt;username&gt;-password.csv *containing the user password is automatically downloaded. For example:

**_testuser-password.csv**

`user,password
testuser,8JGw0FdQbPzwgFC`> Note

For more information on how to generate a new temporary or permanent password for a user, see [Generating a new password for a user](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-users#generating-a-new-password-for-a-user) below.

### Editing a user
- Click on the name of a user to view its details.

or:

Select the user that you want to modify and click **Edit**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Edit the required information.

> Note

For more information on the available fields, see [Creating a user](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-users#creating-a-user) above.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Update**) to confirm.

> Tip

If you make any changes to the user details and then click on a different tab or the **Back **browser button, the system displays the following prompt, allowing you to save, discard, or cancel the changes.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### Generating a new password for a user
- Select the required user and click **Generate Password**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- A confirmation message is displayed, asking you to set the password validity.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Select the preferred option:

**Temporary**: The user will be prompted to change the password at the first login.

- **Permanent**: The password is permanent.

- Click **Generate**. The system generates a new password for the user.

> Note

A CSV file named *_&lt;username&gt;-password.csv *containing the user password is automatically downloaded. For example:

**_testuser-password.csv**

`user,password
testuser,8JGw0FdQbPzwgFC`> Important

It is not possible to generate a new password for SSO users.
